                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/26699: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-24T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 24, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 25—7:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>888. Castillo, Spanish Minister here, strongly intimated to my Belgian colleague
                    a few days ago that the Spanish Government would welcome the presence of strong
                    American forces in proximity to the Spanish Moroccan frontier as a
                    counter-weight to the German forces in German occupied France on the Spanish
                    border.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Madrid and Casablanca.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
